SMSKafkaConsumer
    |
SmsExtractionServiceImpl(This is your orchestrator)
    |
NormalizationServiceImpl(This service is for Normalization)
    |
EntityExtractionServiceImpl(This loads the entities)
    |
EntityExtractionServiceImpl(This extracts the entities)-> This returns the list of CandidateTemplate to the SmsExtractionServiceImpl
    |
TemplateMatchingServiceImpl(TemplateMatchingServiceImpl.match())-> HandlerChain.handle(Chain of Responsibility)->Returns the TemplateMatchOutcome to the SmsExtractionServiceImpl
    |
If hit
SmsExtractionServiceImpl unwraps the TemplateMatchResult:
- match.getTemplate() → the matched LearnedTemplate (has category, subcategory, intent, confidence, List<EntitySnapshot>)
- match.getWinningCandidate() → the CandidateTemplate that produced the hash hit (has the actual extracted values)
    |
Calls TemplateMatchingService.buildExtractedEntities(winningCandidate, learnedTemplate.getEntitySnapshots(), normalizedSms) → maps each
  ExtractedValue to its correct semanticType using EntitySnapshot boundaries → returns Map<String, String> e.g. {TRANSACTION_AMOUNT: "1000", 
  MERCHANT: "SWIGGY"}.
    |
ExtractionResultServiceImpl.save() save the result.



    |
If MISS:-

  matchOutcome.isMatched() = false.

  1. Claim the LLM slot
  SenderLearningStateService.tryClaimLearning(senderId) → Redis setIfAbsent → only one thread wins per sender.

  Losing threads → waitForCompletion(senderId) → parks on Redis pub/sub via CountDownLatch. When winner publishes → wakes up → retries loadEntities +
   extract + match. If hit → returns result. If still miss → competes for next slot.

  2. Pre-LLM check (winning thread)
  Runs retryAfterLearningComplete() one more time — in case another concurrent LLM call just saved the template a millisecond ago. If hit → releases
  lock → returns.
  
  3. Call LLM
  Acquires llmSemaphore. Calls LlmClient.call(normalizedSms, freshEntities) → OpenAiLlmClient builds prompt, calls OpenAI, parses JSON into
  LlmResponse containing List<LlmEntityInfo>, canonical template, category, confidence.
  
  4. Process LLM response
  LlmResponseMapper converts:
  - buildEntitySnapshots(llmResponse) → List<EntitySnapshot>
  - buildExtractedValuesFromLlm(llmResponse, normalizedSms) → List<ExtractedValue> (for hash computation)
  - buildExtractedEntitiesFromLlm(llmResponse) → Map<String,String> (for result)

  HashUtil computes:
  - templateId = SHA256(senderId + "::" + canonicalTemplate)
  - staticTextHash
  - placeholderSequenceHash

  5. Redundancy check
  TemplateMatchingService.existsById(templateId) → checks if another thread already saved this template. If redundant → increments metric but
  continues.

  6. Save template
  TemplateMatchingService.saveTemplate(learnedTemplate) → TemplateRepository → DynamoDB write.

  7. Update entities
  EntityExtractionService.updateGlobalEntities(senderId, existing, llmResponse) → EntityExtractionServiceImpl reloads latest entities from
  EntityRepository, merges new boundary pairs and regex variants (no overwrites), saves back via EntityRepository → DynamoDB write.
  
  8. Release lock and notify
  SenderLearningStateService.setState(LEARNED) → deletes Redis key.
  SenderLearningStateService.publishCompletion(senderId) → publishes to Redis pub/sub → all waiting threads wake up.

  9. Save result and return
  Builds ExtractionResult. Calls ExtractionResultService.save(result) → DynamoDB write. Returns ExtractionResult to SmsKafkaConsumer.

  ---
  Then — Cache Update (Async)
  
  DynamoDB Streams fires on the template + entity writes → Lambda → Redis pub/sub → RedisPubSubSubscriber on all instances → InMemoryCacheUpdater
  updates TemplateCache and EntityCache → all future requests for this sender served from memory.